  <% include ../partials/head %> <!-- including head.ejs -->
  <header>
    <% include ../partials/header %> <!-- including header.ejs -->
  </header>
    <div class="callout large" background="/public/images/banner_image.png">
      <div class="row column text-center align-middle">
		<div class="columns">
			<h1>Display Through Design</h1>
			<p class="lead">A simple portfolio written with nodejs, by Anthony Belton.</p>
		</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row about-me">
      <div class="medium-6 columns medium-push-6">
        <img class="thumbnail" src="/public/images/MainImg.png">
      </div>
      <div class="medium-6 columns medium-pull-6">
        <h2 class="title">A Little About Me</h2>
        <p>Hi there. My name is Anthony. I'm currently studying for my MS in Computer Science from the Georgia Institute of Technology. I welcome you to my online portfolio. I hope to use my online portfolio as a way of connecting others with my resume and accomplishments, and as a way to personally continue to my hobby in web and software development. Here you will be able to see a few examples of my work, both for fun and professionally. If you are interested in contacting me about anything, feel free to visit the <a href="/contact">contact</a> me page.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row my-skills">
      <div class="medium-4 columns contBox">
        <h3 class="title">Photoshop</h3>
        <p>Photoshop, my first love. Designing and slicing up layouts to look pretty on the web is something I've done for a long time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="medium-4 columns contBox">
        <h3 class="title">Javascript</h3>
        <p>Javascript and its various frameworks/libraries is something I've taken a keen interest in these days. From Angular to node, I've found Javascript to be an incredibly dynamic and exciting language to work with.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="medium-4 columns contBox">
        <h3 class="title">Others</h3>
        <p>Some other languages I enjoy working include <strong>Python</strong>, <strong>Java</strong>, and <strong>C#</strong>. Python in particular is one I've familiarized myself with a bit over the last couple of years.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
